commit.message: Do not install in editable mode when testing.
Test on all major click versions.

Bump click dependency to click>=4

It looks like click 3 hasn't worked for a while - or at least the
click-plugins tests don't work on click 3.  Given it was released
4.5 years ago it doesn't seem that risky to bump to click 4.

commit.message: Use latest .gitignore.
Update pytest dependency.  Replace py.test references with pytest.
Test on Python 3.6.  click 7 drops support for Python 3.3

Click 7 changes how command names are generated.

Click generates CLI command names from function names.  Previously a comman function like 'def command_function()' would generate a CLI command called 'command_function'.  As of the commit listed below the CLI commad is now called 'command-function'.

https://github.com/pallets/click/commit/5d1df0e042b2f8b0dee8f6dd9ce74edce331a950
